a hospitalized medical aid worker who volunteered in guinea, one of the three west african nations experiencing an ebola epidemic, and since returned to the united states has tested positive for ebola according to the new york city health department laboratory, which is part of the laboratory response network overseen by the centers for disease control and prevention.the patient has been notified of the test results and remains in isolation. the patient is currently at bellevue hospital in new york city. bellevue hospital is one of eight new york state hospitals that governor cuomo has designated to treat ebola patients. a specially trained cdc team determined earlier this week that the hospital has been trained in proper protocols and is well prepared to treat ebola patients.
